    "title": "Phoenix Rising",
    "description": "&quot;I define hypnotism as the induction of a peculiar psychical [i.e., mental] condition which increases the susceptibility to suggestion. Often, it is true, the [hypnotic] sleep that may be induced facilitates suggestion, but it is not the necessary preliminary. It is suggestion that rules hypnotism....a peculiar condition of the nervous system, induced by a fixed and abstracted attention of the mental and visual eye, on one object, not of an exciting nature.&quot;\n– James Braid, &quot;Beyond the Keynesian Endpoint: Crushed by Credit and Deceived by Debt&quot; (2011)\n\n&quot;First in the ranks see Joan of Arc advance,\nThe scourge of England and the boast of France!\nThough burnt by wicked Bedford for a witch,\nBehold her statue plac'd in glory's niche;\nHer fetters burst, and just releas'd from prison,\nA virgin phoenix from her ashes risen.&quot;\n– Lord Byron\n\n",
